p.span: Our District Mission Statement: Fostered by a cooperative effort between the St. Ansgar School District and community, our mission is to provide the highest quality education in a secure, positive, and challenging environment, empowering all students to reach their full potential.
Our District Vision Statement: Educating every student, every day, with quality learning opportunities.
Our District Motto: Every student, every day; striving to be the best!

span.a: STA School to partner with Northeast Iowa Food Bank to provide the BackPack Program to students during the 2019-2020 school year.

p.span: St. Ansgar School District is seeking public input on our District Developed Service Delivery Plan. To view the plan please click here. Send comments and concerns to: Michael R. Crozier Superintendent of Schools at: mcrozier@st-ansgar.k12.ia.us.

District Office: Michael Crozier, Superintendent, K-12 Director of Special Education

The St. Ansgar Community School District offers career and technical programs in the following service areas: Agriculture, Food and Natural Resources; Business, Finance, Marketing and Management; Applied Science, Technology, Engineering and Manufacturing; and Human Services.

It is the policy of the St. Ansgar Community School District not to discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, sex, disability, religion, creed, age (for employment), marital status (for programs), sexual orientation, gender identity and socioeconomic status (for programs) in its educational programs and its employment practices. The St. Ansgar Community School District affirms its commitment to comply with all applicable federal and state laws, regulations, and orders as required by Iowa Code 216.9 and 256.10 (2), Title VI and VII of the Civil Rights Act of 1964, the Equal Pay Act of 1973, Title IX, Section 504, and the American with Disabilities Act.

If you have any questions or grievances related to compliance with this policy, please contact the St. Ansgar Equity Coordinator, Lynn Baldus, at 206 East 8th St., St. Ansgar, Iowa 50472 or by phone 641-713-4720, email: lbaldus@st-ansgar.k12.ia.us; or the Director of the Office of Civil Rights, U.S. Department of Education, Citigroup Center, 500 W Madison Street, Suite 1475, Chicago, IL 60661-7204, or telephone number 312 730-1560, fax 312 730-1576, email: OCR.Chicago@ed.gov.
